lor:#5382ba;\"><strong>Cremation Bench Estates</strong><br />\r\n					<br />\r\n					A beautiful and elegant way to personalize your family&rsquo;s place of rest. As many as six loved ones may be placed together in one of these custom benches, thus providing for future generations.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n					&nbsp;</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n		</tbody>\r\n	</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<div class=\"breadcrumber\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px; width: 630px; float: left; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); margin-bottom: 20px; padding-bottom: 5px; \">\r\n	<span style=\"color:#5382ba;\">Cemetery &gt;&nbsp;<a id=\"1\" name=\"1\"></a><strong>Cremation Memorialization</strong></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#5382ba;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><strong>Premium Options</strong></span></span></p>','',1309170275,2),(22,22,1,'floral-policy','<div id=\"body_inside\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px; width: 900px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(83, 130, 186); margin-top: 15px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: auto; padding-top: 15px; padding-right: 15px; padding-bottom: 15px; padding-left: 15px; overflow-x: auto; overflow-y: auto; \">\r\n	<div class=\"inside_right_col\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px; width: 630px; float: left; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); \">\r\n		<div class=\"breadcrumber\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px; width: 630px; float: left; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); margin-bottom: 20px; padding-bottom: 5px; \">\r\n			Cemetery &gt;&nbsp;<strong>Floral Policy</strong></div>\r\n		<p><span class=\"subhead\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); font-weight: bold; \">Flower and Decorating Regulations</span></p>\r\n		<p>Memorial Park Cemetery understands and respects the need for families to show respect and love to those interred in our Cemetery through the placement of floral offerings at the gravesite. The following Rules and Regulations regarding flower placement and removal have been enacted in order to preserve the aesthetic beauty of our Cemetery. In addition, these policies will help to ensure the safety of all who visit.</p>\r\n		<p><span class=\"subhead\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); font-weight: bold; \">Flower Placement Policy</span></p>\r\n		<p>Floral arrangements, both fresh-cut and artificial, may be placed at the interment site anytime throughout the year. Memorial Park Cemetery requires arrangements to be placed in the regulation sub-surface bronze vases. We highly encourage the placement of fresh&ndash;cut arrangements; we accept no responsibility or liability for flowers removed or missing.</p>\r\n		<p><span class=\"subhead\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); font-weight: bold; \">Flower Removal Policy</span></p>\r\n		<p>All floral arrangements will be removed from interment spaces when they become unsightly, wilted, discolored or seasonally inappropriate as explained below.</p>\r\n		<p><span class=\"subhead\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); font-weight: bold; \">Holiday and Special Days of Honor</span></p>\r\n		<p><strong>Christmas Season</strong>&ndash; December 1st through January 10th &ndash; Live or artificial flowers or wreaths will be allowed in approved vases, pots, or easels during this time.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong>Potted Plants</strong>&nbsp;are permitted one week before and one week after Easter, Memorial Day Observed, July 4th and Veteran&rsquo;s Day.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong>Flags</strong>&nbsp;are permitted one week before and one week after Memorial Day Observed, July 4th and Veteran&rsquo;s Day. Size maximum allowed is 8&rdquo; x 12&rdquo;, stick maximum height 24&rdquo;.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong>Mausoleum Flowers</strong>&nbsp;will be displayed for three (3) days near the Court of Roses entrance. Flowers, photos, souvenirs, flags or unapproved emblems are prohibited from being placed inside Mausoleum.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong>Burial Service</strong>&nbsp;Flowers will be removed by Cemetery Personnel three (3) days following the service.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong>The following are not permitted during any other time than state above -&nbsp;</strong>Baskets, Potted Plants, Easels or Wreaths.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong>At no time will the following be permitted -&nbsp;</strong>Balloons, Fences, Ceramics, Pumpkins, Statuary, Glass containers or decorations, Shepherd Hooks or windmills.</p>\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		<p><a href=\"http://www.pughs.com/sympathy.htm\" style=\"text-decoration: underline; \" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Pugh Flower\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://www.memorialparkfuneralandcemetery.com/imgs/Pugh_Flowers_newlogo.jpg\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; \" /></a></p>\r\n		<p><br />\r\n			&nbsp;</p>\r\n		<p><strong>Failure to abide by these policies will result in disposal immediately without notice.</strong></p>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n','<div id=\"body_inside\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px; width: 900px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(83, 130, 186); margin-top: 15px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: auto; padding-top: 15px; padding-right: 15px; padding-bottom: 15px; padding-left: 15px; overflow-x: auto; overflow-y: auto; \">\r\n	<div class=\"inside_right_col\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px; width: 630px; float: left; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); \">\r','',1309170588,2),(23,23,1,'what-is-cremation','<div id=\"body_inside\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 16px; width: 900px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(83, 130, 186); margin-top: 15px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: auto; padding-top: 15px; padding-right: 15px; padding-bottom: 15px; padding-left: 15px; overflow-x: auto; overflow-y: auto; \">\r\n	<div class=\"inside_right_col\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 18px; width: 630px; float: left; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); \">\r\n		<div class=\"breadcrumber\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px; width: 630px; float: left; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); margin-bottom: 20px; padding-bottom: 5px; \">\r\n			Cremation &gt;&nbsp;<strong>What is Cremation?</strong></div>\r\n		<div class=\"inside_rc_holder\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 18px; width: 630px; float: left; \">\r\n			<span class=\"subhead\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); font-weight: bold; \">What is the Cremation process?&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n			<p style=\"font-size: 13px; \">Cremation is a process by which intense heat and flame are used to reduce the body to bone fragments which are then processed for final disposition. Contrary to popular belief, cremation offers the widest variety of options for ceremony and memorialization. With a bit of pre-planning, you and your family members can decide on the ceremony and gathering that best meets your needs.</p>\r\n			<span class=\"subhead\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); font-weight: bold; \">Traditional Cremation with Ceremony (visitation prior to act of cremation)</span>\r\n			<p style=\"font-size: 13px; \">This choice involves a full body visitation utilizing a ceremonial container/casket, followed by a religious or private gathering prior to the cremation process described above. After the cremation, the cremated body/ashes are ready for final memorialization, scattering or return to the family. Our Package plans offer a number of unique selections to choose in this category.</p>\r\n			<span class=\"subhead\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); font-weight: bold; \">Ceremonial Cremation (ceremony after the act of cremation)</span>\r\n			<p style=\"font-size: 13px; \">Many who choose cremation do so to forgo the traditional aspects of a full body visitation but still want either a personal ceremonial gathering or religious tribute. Our facilities are perfect for any decision and our package plans offer a number of unique selections to choose in this category.</p>\r\n			<span class=\"subhead\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); font-weight: bold; \">Non-Ceremonial Cremation (simple act of cremation)</span>\r\n			<p style=\"font-size: 13px; \">We take care of bringing the deceased into our care, transportation and the act of cremation. Afterwards, we deliver the cremated body/ashes directly to the person or place you designate.</p>\r\n			<p style=\"font-size: 13px; \"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"color:purple;\"><a href=\"http://www.memorialparkfuneralandcemetery.com/cremation/cremation-memorialization\" style=\"color:purple;\">Memorialization Options</a></span></span></strong></p>\r\n			<p style=\"font-size: 13px; \">Honoring and cherishing the memory of a loved one with a final resting place has long been proven an essential element in the grieving and healing process. Below are some unique selections to choose in this category.</p>\r\n			<span class=\"subhead\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); font-weight: bold; \">In-ground Burial</span>\r\n			<p style=\"font-size: 13px; \">Some prefer to go in for a traditional in-ground burial of the cremated body/ashes and mark the grave with a headstone. Click<span style=\"color:#ee82ee;\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.memorialparkfuneralandcemetery.com/cemetery/in-ground-burial\" style=\"color:purple; \"><span style=\"color:#800080;\"><strong>here</strong></span></a>&nbsp;for pictures and additional description.</p>\r\n			<span class=\"subhead\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); font-weight: bold; \">Permanent Cremation Memorialization</span>\r\n			<p style=\"font-size: 13px; \">Many families find that permanent memorialization in a place and setting specially designed for cremation is the smart and modern way to proceed. Having a personal memorial tribute provides a place to always come back to when the need to remember or feel close arises. Click<span style=\"color:#800080;\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.memorialparkfuneralandcemetery.com/cremation/cremation-memorialization\" style=\"color:purple; \"><span style=\"color:#800080;\"><strong>here</strong></span></a>&nbsp;for pictures and additional description.</p>\r\n			<span class=\"subhead\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); font-weight: bold; \">Scattering and Sharing</span>\r\n			<p style=\"font-size: 13px; \">For some it is important to connect with nature and it is deemed more meaningful to have the cremated body/ashes scattered over land or water. We also offer sharing urns and jewelry for this choice so that small portions of the loved one&rsquo;s cremated remains may be kept physically close to survivors. Of course, choosing memorialization always allows loved ones to come back in the future to obtain additional cremated remains/ashes for future scattering ceremonies or additional jewelry applications. Click<span style=\"color:#800080;\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.memorialparkfuneralandcemetery.com/cremation/cremation-urn\" style=\"color:purple; \"><span style=\"color:#800080;\"><strong>here</strong></span></a><span style=\"color:#800080;\">&nbsp;</span>for pictures and descriptions of sharing choices.</p>\r\n			<span class=\"subhead\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); font-weight: bold; \">Personalized/Custom Arrangements</span>\r\n			<p style=\"font-size: 13px; \">We offer families the opportunity to remember their loved ones in special ways. These include inscribing names and sayings on tree plaques or a choice of urns to hold the remains for display at home. For other requests, we are always at your service to meet your specific needs.</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<br />\r\n','<div id=\"body_inside\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 16px; width: 900px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(83, 130, 186); margin-top: 15px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: auto; padding-top: 15px; padding-right: 15px; padding-bottom: 15px; padding-left: 15px; overflow-x: auto; overflow-y: auto; \">\r\n	<div class=\"inside_right_col\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 18px; width: 630px; float: left; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); \">\r','',1309171018,2),(37,37,1,'wedding-information','<div id=\"body_inside\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px; width: 900px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(83, 130, 186); margin-top: 15px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: auto; padding-top: 15px; padding-right: 15px; padding-bottom: 15px; padding-left: 15px; overflow-x: auto; overflow-y: auto; \">\r\n	<div class=\"inside_right_col\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px; width: 630px; float: left; color: rgb(83, 130, 186); \">\r\n		<div class=\"breadcrumber\